        <updateDate>2016-04-19T20:45:22Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Strengthening the Department of Homeland Security Secure Mail Initiative Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Homeland Security to provide an option under the Secure Mail Initiative under which, for payment of a fee recouping costs, a person to whom a document is sent under such initiative may require the U.S. Postal Service to obtain a signature from that person in order to deliver the document.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
